As a content marketing specialist, you're a key member of Europe's demand generation team, where you'll take up the mantle of content producer and strategist. You will ideate, strategize on, and execute content creation for all stages of the buyer journey. You'll become intimately familiar with our product and will excel at expressing the value of our solution in a succinct, yet compelling way towards the different audiences that we speak to. From C-Suite executives to practitioners in their respective fields of technology or operations, you'll understand their most urgent concerns and interests, and you'll be able to provide them with valuable insights on the latest trends in the region, helpful guides that empower them to take action, and thoughtful perspectives to educate and inspire them.



As part of a multi-disciplinary Scrum team, you'll work together with other marketing specialists, including a digital marketer and a visual designer, while reporting to the Head of Marketing. You will also be part of the Communications Guild, where you'll contribute to evolving our content marketing best practices and be able to consult with the other content experts in the department to hone your craft. You'll collaborate closely with the Sales, Partner and Customer Success teams. Your passion for storytelling and content marketing will help drive dialogue with customers and prospects and support the demand generation goals in Europe.



Excited to do your best work at a supportive company that's willing to push the limits? Then read on.


**Meet the job**
----------------



Your key responsibilities


* Content strategy and creation - You will lead the content creation process, from strategy through to execution. You have a strong understanding of how to align, tweak and evolve the messaging for different personas, at different stages of the funnel, as well as for different channels. You will be the strategic content partner in Europe, proposing the different content assets needed to meet marketing goals, and will be responsible for delivering them.


Measure and improve content performance - You have a holistic approach to content and understand that your job isn't done simply when the words are written; you'll work closely with the designer to ensure that the final deliverable is formatted for optimal readability, and with the digital marketer to optimize it for maximum impact. You'll measure the impact of your content, analyze its performance and continuously look to improve it to meet (and exceed) campaign goals. You're committed to delivering content of the highest standards of quality in every way;
* Be the voice of the customer - The journalist in you loves talking to our colleagues in Sales and Customer Success, to our partners, and customers. You're hungry for knowledge and will proactively read up on the latest technology, business and fintech news to identify opportunities for content angles that we should jump on;


* Writing - You're the Swiss Army Knife of content writing, and are equally comfortable writing thoughtful long-form content such as ebooks, blog posts, and case studies, or in shorter, high-conversion copy such as ads and landing pages. You're also able to switch gears and take on more creative assets with ease, such as video scripts and event collateral. You will be one of the guardians of our brand's tone of voice, and will be a relentless perfectionist when it comes to grammar; you'll spot every single typo and errant punctuation mark in any content piece. Above all, you'll ensure that everything you deliver is engaging, compelling, and well worth the time for busy bankers to read.




